Construction on a light rail route connecting China's Macao Special Administrative Region and Hengqin Island in neighboring Guangdong Province began on Wednesday.The 2.2-kilometer-long line starts from an elevated station in Macao and culminates at an underground station in front of Hengqin Port. It will help enhance regional cooperation within the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area, adding Macao to its "one-hour living circle."